        <num>CC 1845</num>
        <heading>1845.  Confirmation of donation</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1845.  Confirmation of donation
A donation inter vivos that is null for lack of proper form may be confirmed by the donor but the confirmation must be made in the form required for a donation.
The universal successor of the donor may, after his death, expressly or tacitly confirm such a donation.</p>
        </content>
